import React, { useEffect } from 'react'; import '../styles/components.css'; const Resume = () => { useEffect(() => { // Function to handle legend item hover interactions const setupChartInteractions = () => { const legendItems = document.querySelectorAll('.legend-item'); legendItems.forEach(item => { // Get the class name of the color span to identify which segment to highlight const colorSpan = item.querySelector('.legend-color'); if (!colorSpan) return; // Extract the class that identifies the segment (e.g., 'python', 'aws', etc.) const segmentClass = Array.from(colorSpan.classList) .find(cls => cls !== 'legend-color'); if (!segmentClass) return; // Add mouse enter event listener item.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => { // Find the corresponding chart segment const segment = document.querySelector(`.chart-segment.segment-${segmentClass}`); if (segment) { segment.classList.add('segment-highlighted'); } }); // Add mouse leave event listener item.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => { // Remove highlight from the segment const segment = document.querySelector(`.chart-segment.segment-${segmentClass}`); if (segment) { segment.classList.remove('segment-highlighted'); } }); }); }; // Call the setup function after a short delay to ensure DOM is fully loaded const timer = setTimeout(() => { setupChartInteractions(); }, 500); // Cleanup function return () => { clearTimeout(timer); // Remove event listeners if component unmounts const legendItems = document.querySelectorAll('.legend-item'); legendItems.forEach(item => { item.removeEventListener('mouseenter', () => {}); item.removeEventListener('mouseleave', () => {}); }); }; }, []); return (
